Producing HTML output

# if my-html-styles.xsl includes docbook.xsl
#xsltproc --output dp-um.html my-html-styles.xsl dp-um.xml
xsltproc --output html/index.html my-html-styles.xsl deepskylog_nl.docbook

# if my-html-styles.xsl includes chunk.xsl
xsltproc my-html-styles.xsl dp-um.xml


Producing JavaHelp output

$ xsltproc my-javahelp-styles.xsl dp-um.xml

# optionally you can regenerate the HTML output in order to have headers and
# footers with Prev/Next links.
$ xsltproc my-html-styles.xsl dp-um.xml

$ jhelp --hs file:jhelpset.hs --id ch01 



Produce a PDF file

$ xsltproc --output dp-um.fo --stringparam fop.extensions 1 my-fo-styles.xsl dp-um.xml
$ fop -fo dp-um.fo -pdf dp-um.pdf
$ acroread dp-um.pdf



Profile - include or exclude certain section/chapters of the documentation

We have assigned the 'instrument' attribute to some of the sections specific for
PACS, HIFI or SPIRE. Making a document with only the common parts and those
specific for HIFI, do the following:

$ xsltproc --output hifi.xml --stringparam  profile.attribute  "instrument" --stringparam profile.value "hifi" /software/share/docbook/docbook-xsl/profiling/profile.xsl dp-um.xml
$ xsltproc my-html-styles.xsl hifi.xml




+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

Converting the XML code

$ ./convert <filename>.xml

# the s is introduced manually for each para that should be replaced by screen.
# This is for single line screen areas.
$ perl -pi -e 's#<spara>(.*?)</para>#<screen>$1</screen>#g;' <filename>.xml

The convert script does the following:

#!/usr/bin/perl -pi
s/<phrase.*?>//g;
s/<section>/$&\n/g;
s#<para/>##g;
s/&#x2013;/-/g;
s/&#x201[CD];/"/g;
s/&#x2026;/.../g;
s/&#x201[89];/'/g;
s/<para>/\n$&/g;
s/<listitem>/\n$&/g;
s/IA&gt;&gt;/&prompt;/g;
s/IA>>/&prompt;/g;

Run this script only once on an XML file or it will produce more unwanted
newlines.

In JEdit replace in a selection the </?para> where there should not be any e.g.
within a screen area.


